is quantized.

00:45:07.960 --> 00:45:10.910
Now quantization had already
been annunciated by

00:45:10.910 --> 00:45:12.880
Max Planck in 1909.

00:45:12.880 --> 00:45:17.090
You see, the classical theory
of radiation gave this

00:45:17.090 --> 00:45:20.110
prediction for intensity as
a function of wavelength.

00:45:20.110 --> 00:45:23.400
They called this the
explosion, the

00:45:23.400 --> 00:45:24.490
collapse of the theory.

00:45:24.490 --> 00:45:27.020
As you go to low wavelength,
the intensity

00:45:27.020 --> 00:45:28.420
goes without abatement.

00:45:28.420 --> 00:45:31.100
But these are the spectra
that were measured.

00:45:31.100 --> 00:45:34.590
Depending on the temperature
of the gas, you get this

00:45:34.590 --> 00:45:35.360
distribution.

00:45:35.360 --> 00:45:39.150
So how to get the distribution
to turn around at lower values

00:45:39.150 --> 00:45:40.040
of wavelength?

00:45:40.040 --> 00:45:43.070
And in order to do that, Planck
suggested that light is

00:45:43.070 --> 00:45:46.370
composed of energy packets,
or quanta.

00:45:46.370 --> 00:45:52.590
That light is a stream of
individual energy bits.

00:45:52.590 --> 00:45:55.460
And the elementary unit of
electromagnetic radiation is

00:45:55.460 --> 00:45:57.490
the photon.

00:45:57.490 --> 00:45:58.780
And you can say, well I don't
understand, where

00:45:58.780 --> 00:46:00.000
